  "texts": [
    "Generative models present a promising approach to small molecule generation, which is key in lead identification.",
    "They address the challenge of determining the set of molecules that satisfy a desired set of properties.",
    "Generative models are trained to identify the underlying patterns and structures within the training dataset, in order to generate new instances that share similar characteristics with the molecules in the training data.",
    "A type of generative model called diffusion model is used by Hoogeboom et al.",
    "for generating 3D structures of small molecules from noisy SMILES or structural data (Hoogeboom et al. 2022)."
  ],
